constructive and positive part in a direction of travel </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">to </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">which all the major countries are now committed in terms of transparency and accountability and financial services.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold">Q9 </span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Andy McDonald: </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">In the light of </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">t</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">he fact that there were those discussions, if these remarks were careless or inaccurate</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> do you think that that has damaged the relationship between the UK and the Crown Dependencies</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> or has that been overcome by these discussions?</span><br /><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 14.2pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Lord McNally</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">: I hope not. The Crown Dependencies have certainly expressed thanks for the way that the Prime Minister has handled recent multinational G8 and G20 meetings. The nature of the relationship is </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">that </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">sometimes they will say things or do things that upset us</span><span style="font-family:Garamond;