of entrustment it does happen</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> because essent</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">ially what happened over the FA</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">C</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">A agreement with the United States</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">—</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">can I put it to you this way</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">?—</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">is that</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> when </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">entrustment was sought for this agreement, the UK Government effectively said, </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">“We rather like this idea. </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">You can</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">t have entrustment until you have a treaty with us on the same lines</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">.”</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> Is bargaining still a feature of entrustment?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 14.2pt; text-align:justify"><br /><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Lord McNally</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">: I would say yes. Is that short enough as well?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold">Q29 </span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><spa