ont-size:12pt">one message from the </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">United Kingdom</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold">Q33 </span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Chair: </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">United Kingdom</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> is the </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">United Kingdom</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">:</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> it is not the Crown Dependencies. Does that mean you go into negotiations saying, </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">“T</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">he United Kingdom thinks this</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">,” and say</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> nothing at al</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">l about the Crown Dependencies in an issue where</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> they are a central player</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> as in the Icelandic banking crisis?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 14.2pt; text-align:justify"><br /><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Lord McNally</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">: Where they are a central player then it is obvious and I would hope that we would take fully on board their interests</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">,</span><s